        "title": "test(tools): add unmocked image custom-provider auth regression",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `image-tool.custom-provider-auth.proof.test.ts` to cover the user-reported custom-provider image auth bug with **unmocked** `model-auth` and helper wiring.\n- Exercises config-only `models.providers.<id>.apiKey` auth through `hasProviderAuthForTool`, `resolveImageModelConfigForTool`, production image-tool factory availability, and deferred `execute` with real `getApiKeyForModel`.\n- Includes negative coverage when `apiKey` is missing, plus a regression note for the pre-fix `hasAuthForProvider`-only candidate filter.\n\nFollow-up to #85570. Existing `image-tool.test.ts` coverage mocks `model-auth`, so it cannot prove the shipped auth resolution path end-to-end.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/image-tool.custom-provider-auth.proof.test.ts`\n\nBehavior addressed: custom provider vision models configured only via `models.providers.<id>.apiKey` should auto-discover and execute on the deferred image tool path without env keys or auth profiles.\nReal environment tested: Linux source checkout on latest `main` with Node 22.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/image-tool.custom-provider-auth.proof.test.ts`\nEvidence after fix: 6/6 tests passed in the new proof file (Vitest run on branch head).\nObserved result after fix: config-backed custom provider auth resolves image model config, registers the tool, resolves runtime API key from config, and executes without \"No image model is configured\".\nWhat was not tested: live gateway/channel roundtrip, e2e-go smoke, or changes outside the new regression test file.",
